      "content": "A good buffer time between the Heathrow Express and the LNER train, say at least 45 minutes, is wise. This gives you enough room for a minor delay on the Express, or if the platform for the LNER is a bit of a mess, you won't be scrambling. It's better to have a little extra time than to be stuck waiting for a train that's already been delayed. Always keep an eye on the departure boards, though.",
